==English==
===Etymology===
[[poly-]] + [[domino|(d)omino]], as if the ''d'' were for [[di-]], two, as a domino is made up of two squares

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''polyomino''' (''plural'' '''polyominoes''')

#{{mathematics}} A [[geometric]] [[shape]] made from one or more [[square]]s joined edge to edge in various [[arrangement]]s.

